> If loadlin can load linux from under DOS, and BootX can load 
> linux from
> under MacOS, is it possible to write something similar that 
> runs linux?
> 
Take a look at "User Mode Linux" 
http://user-mode-linux.sourceforge.net/.
It's not quite what you want, but it's somewhere in the same ballpark. It's
a port of the Linux kernel to itself (a kernel that runs under another Linux
kernel in user mode).
